results.name: Triangle T(n,k) giving number of symmetric polynomials of degree n in k noncommuting variables, n >=2, 2 <= k <= n.
reference: M. C. Wolf, Symmetric Functions of Non-commutative Elements, Duke Math. J., 2 (1936), 626-637.
example: T(1,1)=1 from Sum x_1; T(2,2)=1 from Sum x_1 x_2; T(3,2)=1 from Sum x_1 x_2 x_1; T(3,3)=1 from Sum x_1 x_2 x_3; ...
